{"parse":{"title":"Tense confusion","pageid":38355520,"revid":588847923,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-globalize\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"Globe icon.\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/48px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png\" width=\"48\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/73px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/97px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"350\" data-file-height=\"290\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">The examples and perspective in this article <b>may not represent a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Countering_systemic_bias\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Countering systemic bias\">worldwide view</a> of the subject</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> You may <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Tense_confusion&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a>, discuss the issue on the <a href=\"/wiki/Talk:Tense_confusion\" title=\"Talk:Tense confusion\">talk page</a>, or <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Article_wizard\" title=\"Wikipedia:Article wizard\">create a new article</a>, as appropriate.</span>  <small><i>(July 2013)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Grammar\" title=\"Grammar\">grammar</a>, a <b>tense confusion</b> occurs when a writer shifts from the <a href=\"/wiki/Present_tense\" title=\"Present tense\">present tense</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/Past_tense\" title=\"Past tense\">past tense</a> (or vice versa).<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  For example, in the following example, the change from \"saw\" (past tense) to \"is\" (present tense) represents a tense confusion:\n</p><p>Example:\n</p>\n<blockquote><p>He <i>saw</i> that she <i>is</i> very tall.</p></blockquote>\n<p>It is important to avoid tense confusions because they hurt reader comprehension.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Grammerly_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Grammerly-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  They are a common grammatical error,<sup id=\"cite_ref-CLA_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CLA-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> especially among beginning writers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tense_confusion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www3.uark.edu/qwct/resources/handouts/19%20Verb%20Tenses%20-%20Correcting%20Shifts.pdf\">\"Verb Tenses ~ Correcting Shifts\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. The Quality Writing Center<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">28 January</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Verb+Tenses+~+Correcting+Shifts&amp;rft.pub=The+Quality+Writing+Center&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww3.uark.edu%2Fqwct%2Fresources%2Fhandouts%2F19%2520Verb%2520Tenses%2520-%2520Correcting%2520Shifts.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATense+confusion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://grammar.ccc.commnet.edu/grammar/consistency.htm\">\"Tense Consistency\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Tense+Consistency&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgrammar.ccc.commnet.edu%2Fgrammar%2Fconsistency.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATense+confusion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.towson.edu/ows/tenseconsistency.htm\">\"Verb Tense Consistency\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2013-01-28</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Verb+Tense+Consistency&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.towson.edu%2Fows%2Ftenseconsistency.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATense+confusion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Grammerly-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Grammerly_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">